lied() method which recursively checks if all replaced migrations (including those transitively replaced by other squashed migrations) have been applied in the database.\n\nAdditional supporting files include:\n- django/db/migrations/migration.py: Defines the Migration base class with the `replaces` attribute\n- django/db/migrations/optimizer.py: Optimizes operations sequences during squash generation\n- django/db/migrations/exceptions.py: Defines exception types (NodeNotFoundError, InconsistentMigrationHistory, CircularDependencyError) used for validation\n- django/db/migrations/writer.py: Serializes and writes migration files\n- django/db/migrations/recorder.py: Records applied migration status in the database\n\nThe entire flow ensures that squashed migrations can coexist with their replaced migrations, Django intelligently switches between them based on migration history state, and circular dependency scenarios are detected and prevented."
